<h2 id="section-top">Physiotherapy</h2>
</div>
<div class="col four-sm">
</div>
<div class="col three-sm" id="ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_PlaceHolderMain_contentColumn1">
<div class="box">
<p class="module">
        This Department is managed by  
        <a href="/Services/Trusts/Overview/DefaultView.aspx?id=1664">Dartford and Gravesham NHS Trust</a>
</p>
<div class="panel">
<div class="panel-content">
<div class="pad clear">
<div class="service-locations clear">
<div class="panel edit-box">
<div class="panel-content">
<div class="pad clear">
<p class="address"><br/>01322 428587</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="panel">
<div class="panel-content">
<div class="pad clear">
<div id="imageContentd7de86d01dc54875835134d1f3cc7956">
<div class="profile-pic">
<img alt="Physiotherapy" border="0" id="ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_PlaceHolderMain_column1Content_column1Content_SummaryAndPhotoModule_PhotoView_DisplayImage" src="/Services/UserControls/UploadHandlers/MediaServerHandler.ashx?id=41396"/>
</div>
</div>
<p>Physiotherapy is the fourth largest healthcare profession in the world. It is a clinical specialty that assesses and treats problems with movement, dysfunction and pain. These can arise from musculoskeletal, neurological, respiratory and chronic disability conditions, or from mental illness and intellectual impairment.</p>
<p>To contact the DVH department telephone 01322 428587 or for Hydrotherapy 01322 428590.</p>
<p>The Darent Valley Hospital provides a service to several different areas and specialities, including:</p>
<ul>
<li>OrthopaedicÂ physiotherapy.</li>
<li>Inpatient physiotherapy.</li>
<li>Outpatient physiotherapy.</li>
<li>Neurological rehabilitation.</li>
<li>Hydrotherapy.</li>
</ul></div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
